<!-- Main Content -->
<div class="container">
  <h1 class="title text-center">Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) System</h1>
  
  <div class="description">
    <h3>Welcome to the RBAC Application built with Node.js, Express, and MongoDB!</h3> <br>
    <p style="font-size: 25px;">This application helps manage users, roles, and permissions with dynamic access control based on roles like Admin, Moderator, and User.</p>
    <br>
    <h4 style="font-size: 1.8em;">Key Features:</h4> <br>
    <ul>
      <li><b>User Management:</b> Manage user accounts and their status.</li>
      <li><b>Role Management:</b> Define and assign roles with permissions.</li>
      <li><b>Permissions:</b> Assign Read, Write, Delete permissions to roles.</li>
    </ul>
    <br>
    <p style="font-size: 1.8em; color: #3c4b76;";>This App uses:</p> <br>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Node.js</b> & <b>Express</b> for routing.</li>
      <li><b>Passport.js</b> for email/password authentication.</li>
      <li><b>Mongoose</b> for MongoDB data storage.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  
  <div class="features">
    <h3>Core Features:</h3> <br>
    <ol>
      <li><b>User Management:</b> Admins can create, edit, and delete users.</li>
      <li><b>Role Management:</b> Define roles (Admin, Moderator, User) with permissions.</li>
      <li><b>Access Control:</b> Modify user access based on assigned roles.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  
</div>

